Kogi State Deputy Governor Simon Achuba has said his security details earlier withdrawn have been restored. Achuba had on Sunday raised the alarm that his life and those of his family members were in danger following the withdrawal of all his security details by the ADC to the state governor. In a statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Akor Sylvester, he said his security details had been restored in full yesterday night and had since resumed duties. He commended the Acting Inspector General of Police and the Kogi State Commissioner of Police for their prompt responses to his call.  Kogi deputy governor's security details restored My life in danger – Kogi dep gov Kogi: Achuba sworn in as Bello’s deputy